{
 "$schema": "./_schema.md#names",
 "note": "Weighted vocabulary for vessel names. The generator picks a theme allowed for the vessel's {power, role}, draws a stem, then applies the construction rule (navalPrefix + article) from powers.json. `themesByPower` maps power ids to the theme pools they may draw from. Naval and merchant draw from different pools. Keep stems period-plausible. `captains` gives each spawning culture a shipmaster pool (feature pass 3): European cultures compose given+surname; Indian-Ocean cultures carry the nakhoda title in the name (the shipowner-master of the dhow and Mughal marine); Ottoman masters are '<given> Reis' with Greek kapetans alongside (the empire's marine was substantially Greek-crewed); East-Asian pools are surname-first or full names. Captains draw from their OWN RNG sub-stream — see world.js makeCaptain.",
